reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy design and space saver
reviews.reviewText: I like it very much. It is very easy to set up and it works very well. Every time when I finish washing the dishes just put them on it, it dries very quick. It also helps save so much spcace. Most Important, it is made of metal and the quality is good. After having this, my kitchen becomes neat and tidy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars sturdy design and ample space
reviews.reviewText: The sink dish drying rack exceeded my expectations. Its sturdy design and ample space make it a kitchen essential. The clever drainage system keeps countertops dry, and the versatile layout accommodates various dish sizes. A sleek and functional addition to any kitchen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Space Saver & Lots of Added Utility
reviews.reviewText: I just purchased a house that has a smaller kitchen than I'm use to and needed to find a dish rack that doesn't take up much countertop space. I'm so glad I found this over the sink rack! It opens up so much extra space and adds a new shelf to store larger kitchen items (or oddly shaped items)!Three small things I love about it:-This rack comes with a small basket for sponges, soap, etc. which keeps my sponges clean & dry when not in use-There are separate slots to keep utensils from kitchen knives so you don't have to worry about your kiddos accidentally grabbing the wrong thing and cutting themself.-It comes with a spot to put cutting boards/lids vertically which helps them dry quickly AND keeps them from taking up a lot of unnecessary real estate

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Gets the job done!
reviews.reviewText: So glad I bought this gadget.Pros:More counter space now that I don’t need drying racks taking up space.Looks awesome, makes me feel like a middle aged boss lady.Once assembled, seems pretty sturdy.Dishes, cutting boards, knives, etc all have a convenient home and place to air dry without making my house look extremely disorganized.Makes my adhd cleaning fits 10/10 more fun when this thing makes my kitchen look this sophisticated.Cons:I cut the crap outta my hand pulling this guy out of the box. It’s clear that manufacturing is speedy and cheap, as there are MANY sharp corners on parts, so assemble carefully. The metal is strong and seems sturdy, but also the screws dented screw holes just from hand-tightening them with the provided Allen wrench. I’ll definitely be avoiding any overloading, but then I really only wanted it for the dishes that don’t make it into the dishwasher when it’s full or already running.I haven’t needed to yet, but I imagine that the plastic/clear panels will require cleaning and I can already tell just by how lightweight they are that it will require extra care to avoid damaging them by mistake.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Frees up counter space and organizes your space, build quality subpar
reviews.reviewText: Overall, this dish rack frees up a lot of counter space and is one of the nicer designs compared to the rest on Amazon. However, the dish rack itself doesn't fit large plates, and doesn’t look like it can hold a lot of weight.Assembling was not a breeze! There were some panel gaps about 2-3 millimeters on the shelf and door. As much as I tried to disassemble and reassemble, I came to conclusion the screw holes must be misaligned. Although a minor design flaw, the worse part was the plastic drip tray which was completely warped and not at all useable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Definitely a must need in small kitchens!!!
reviews.reviewText: I wish I would have ordered this year's ago! I've lived in my house for almost 20 years. The kitchen is very small and I don't have many cabinets! This is the best product I have bought in years! It's very sturdy! The suction cups on the bottom of the legs work to well! We tried to move it after putting it together and it was hard to get the suction loose!😂 It's very sturdy! Its also super easy to put together! It took me probably 15 minutes at max! I moved all my dishes to it and put my mixer and coffee pot on top. I'm not worried at all! I believe it can hold a lot more weight! I love it has a spot to store my cutting board. If you have thinner cutting boards you can store multiple! I love all the extra little storage spaces that comes with it, the knife box, the soap tray, the box for other utensils, and the hooks I hang my measuring spoons from. I definitely recommend this strainer! I use it as a strainer and a cupboard for my dishes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I love it. I needed somewhere to dry my dishes and didn’t like how most of them take over most of the counter. This is so nice looking and does the job I need without taking up space I need for other things. I love how it has the door and covers, makes things feel so much more tidy.
